commitResults.messageTitle: Modify Duke to convert deadline and event time ranges to LocalDatetime objects
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, Duke saves the deadline and event time
ranges as String objects to Deadline and Event objects.

Now, Duke validates and parses user inputs to these
datetimes to LocalDateTime objects and saves them to
Deadline and Event objects.

commitResults.messageBody:
This ensures that the datetime string, obtained from parsing the user input, is not empty.
If it is empty, then Parser validation has failed to detect this.

This prevents empty deadline datetime from being saved to storage.

commitResults.messageBody:
This ensures that the datetime string, obtained from parsing the user input,
is not empty. If it is empty, then Parser validation has failed to detect this.

This prevents empty Event start, end datetimes and date range from being saved
to storage.
